column2: we have celebrated radical inclusivity with human beings on night club stages you wouldn‚Äôt typically find at performance venues. we dance to advocate self love for those too afraid to be who they are. we dance to tell the world we don‚Äôt need permission to be who we are. but we cannot call ourselves radically inclusive unless we advocate with intersectionality. we cannot confront fat shaming without denouncing racism. we cannot champion gender equity without defending trans rights. we cannot debunk mental health myths without calling out ableism. we cannot dismantle systems of oppression without acknowledging all who are oppressed. today we have the opportunity to vote changes into these systems. we encourage you to celebrate that right. and to do so without condemning those who won‚Äôt
column3: those who don‚Äôt because these systems will continue to marginalize them regardless of today‚Äôs outcome. voting is only one small step. we invite you to join us as we climb the other 364 days a year to make change happen for all. so that every single human can some day say they don‚Äôt need permission to be who they are. üåè

the reason i started this very personal project back in 2014 was because i wanted to open the conversations i‚Äôd not had amongst my closest friends. i never anticipated that i would receive 100 responses (that is how our name was born) nor that this project would turn into this incredible community. thank you all for making me feel less alone.
thank you to everyone who has supported us along the way. survivors and our allies. we are in this together and we are standing strong in solidarity.

column1: 252586;instagram;2018-11-06 04:13:52;FALSE;"6 years ago i committed to running a marathon as a non-runner.
5 years ago i had never swam a single lap in my life but committed to learn to swim so i could do a sprint triathlon.
3 years ago i crossed my first ironman finish line.
1 year ago i crossed my second.

next year i will cross my third and this time it‚Äôs more personal than ever. 10 months left in this journey which seems like a long time but in reality with everything else planned and training and life ... next september will be here before i know it.
i can‚Äôt wait to feel this same joy as in the picture above ... racing in a sport i love once again.
just a reminder this is our hobby and for fun. if you need to take time away for personal reasons
column2: it‚Äôs ok. if you miss some training sessions because life is too busy but you fit in most training sessions ... don‚Äôt even think twice. just keep focused and dedicated. no matter if you‚Äôre chasing finish lines or finish times. we all got this and work our asses off. it‚Äôs inspiring and encouraging to watch your stories and highs and lows. it‚Äôs going to be an exciting road to #ironmanchattanooga but

column1: 252621;instagram;2018-11-06 03:26:03;FALSE;"when you silence the helpers you silence the help --- .
warning: if you don't feel this post is for you

as humans most of us are doing our best to do the right thing. when we know better we have the ability to do better. that's the goal. along the way we mess up and fail but we also learn and grow. we don't know what we don't know. .
here's my point... when you see a bunch of ""helpers"" (humans doing their best to do the right thing) support them. even when they mess up. no one is perfect and no that's not an excuse
column2: it's a reality. because even those judging the helpers are messing up too. there will be some humans who will choose not to support the helpers and that's ok. as for the rest of us
column3: let's keep dismantling the patriarchal system by helping those who are working to dismantle it
column4: and all the garbage that comes with it. .

column1: being compassionate means you see the intention
column2: the integrity and even the blind spots that some of the helpers don't yet see. humans can rant
column3: rage and vent but when it comes to helpers helping others
column4: some of us need to stay on board and support that!!! that's how we keep each other connected
column5: inspired and hopeful. compassion for ""us"" (all of us) lights the way for forgiveness
column6: understanding and new beginnings for everyone. .

column1: we're all in this together. so instead of criticizing the helpers who are trying desperately to get on board let's do our best to keep helping them
column2: help others who need the help. let's hold each other with grace and let that grace see us through to a place where all the world's people are loved and valued
column3: each as much as the other. and the world shall be one üíóüåéüíó #iloveus

""take on""  as a reality .. or even a possibility - least not one of any organized religion - i think and believe the inspiring aspect of janira is her authenticity .. her fight .. her great endurance .. and the jenira determination to include others - help others .. fight for others no matter how hard life is for oneself .. life hands some of us lemons and we make sure others have nutrition
